      • findAllByProperty

        public Iterable<T> findAllByProperty(String key,
                                     Object value,
                                     boolean filterByType)
        Allows optional filtering by model type, because getVertices(prop, value, type) does not filter by model type (it only frames the vertex as that type). That can be used to prevent collisions if multiple models use the same property name (e.g. "name").
        Parameters:
        filterByType - If true, the items returned from the graph are further filtered by this service's model type.
